fields.itinerary:
The major stops and attractions: 
  1. Rome to Florence
    We will pick you up from any hotel in Rome at your appointed location and time. To utilize the maximum of your time you need to start your tour between 07:30 am and 08:30 am. 
  2. Piazzale Michelangelo
    Upon arrival in Florence after a 3-hour journey, visit Piazzale Michelangelo, where you can enjoy a complete view of the entire city. This place has the power to create memories that will last a lifetime. 
  3. Duomo- Cathedrale di  Santa Maria del Fiore
    After visiting the Piazzale Michelangelo you will go to Duomo best iconic landmark in the city. Which is the amazing pink, white, and green marble facade, along with the graceful bell tower, dominates the Renaissance cityscape.
  4. Ponte Vecchio
    At Ponte Vecchio, you will discover ancient history. This bridge is the only ancient structure crossing the river Anto. Where you can experience shopping.
  5. Palazzo Vecchio The Palazzo Vecchio is one of the most famous symbols in Florence which is used as the residence and workplace of republic officials. After visiting the Ponte Vecchio and Palazzo Vecchio, Enjoy the taste of many Tuscan delicious regional wines in the local Florentine restaurant at lunchtime.
  6. Basilica of Santa Croce
    Basilica Santa Croce where you can discover the final resting land of the greatest minds and artistic visionaries like Dante and Michelangelo, infusing Santa Croce with unique wisdom and boundless creativity.

fields.itinerary:
The major stops and attractions:

  • Process for Rome to Florence
    Get ready for an exciting start to your tour! We'll pick you up from your preferred location in Rome and time. It could be from any hotel in Rome.
    Duration: 3 hours
    Pass by
  • Piazzale Michelangelo
    You will enjoy the complete view of the city from above, just the moment you arrive in Florence! Enjoy the stop at Piazzale Michelangelo, the perfect location to take memorable pictures! Few places are so compact or so packed with incredible art and architectural masterpieces on every corner of the city.
    Duration: 15 minutes
    Admission is free
  • Duomo - Cattedrale di Santa Maria del Fiore
    Admire the breathtaking beauty of the Duomo of Florence! The Santa Maria del Fiore Cathedral is one of the most iconic landmarks in the city. Built by Filippo Brunelleschi's red-tiled dome, it's a staggering construction. The amazing pink, white and green marble facade, along with the graceful bell tower, dominates the Renaissance cityscape.
    Duration: 30 minutes
    Admission ticket is not included
  • Ponte Vecchio
    Explore the Ponte Bridge, which stands as the symbol of Florence and the only ancient architecture crossing the river Arno, is full of local fashion and boutique jewelry. Italian fashion is born in Florence. Spend some time there and enjoy shopping at famous fashion houses and local family-run workshops (workshops) in a glorious tangle of medieval backstreets.
    Duration: 15 minutes
    Admission is free
  • Basilica of Santa Croce
    Explore the Basilica of Santa Croce. This wonderful place is the final resting land of the greatest minds artistic visionaries like Dante and Michelangelo, infusing Santa Croce with unique wisdom and boundless creativity. You won't want to miss experiencing the unique place of this wonderful location.
    Duration: 30 minutes
    Admission is free
  • It’s time for food — a typical Tuscan lunch.
    Duration: 60 minutes
    Lunch cost not included
  • Process for Florence to Pisa
    Start an exciting journey to Pisa after ending your Florence tour with an enjoyable lunch.
    Duration: 60 minutes
    Pass by
  • Piazza dei Miracoli
    Admire the square which hosts the Leaning Tower, the Baptistery and the Cathedral of Pisa at your own pace. Have you always dreamed of taking pictures in front of the Leaning Tower of Pisa? Then you will get plenty of time to explore the UNESCO Heritage Site Leaning Tower independently and take photos in front of the wonderful tower. Baptistery of San Giovanni Explore the Baptistery of San Giovanni that stands in front of the Cathedral and is the ancient religious and civil center of the city, as well as a masterpiece of Italian Romanesque.
    90minutes
    Admission ticket free
  • Back To Rome
    After enjoying a full day, it's time to head back from Florence to Rome. Duration: 4 hours
    Pass by

fields.itinerary:
1. London to Amsterdam

    Start your adventure with a scenic canal cruise through Amsterdam's historic waterways, followed by a visit to Zaanse Schans, a quaint village famous for its windmills and traditional crafts. Savor Dutch cheeses at a local cheese factory and explore the city's vibrant streets on a walking tour.

  2. Amsterdam to Brussels to Paris

    Head to Brussels to marvel at the Atomium, visit a historic castle, and stroll through the Grand Place while tasting Belgian chocolates. Continue to Paris, where the City of Lights awaits.

  3. Paris – Disneyland Magic

    Explore Paris on a guided city walking tour, passing iconic landmarks like the Champs-Élysées and Arc de Triomphe. Spend the afternoon immersed in the wonder of Disneyland Paris.

  4. Paris to London

    Sail along the Seine on a relaxing canal cruise and visit the Eiffel Tower’s second stage for breathtaking views. Conclude your journey as you return to London with unforgettable memories.

fields.itinerary:
1. Welcome to Reykjavik The Land of Fire and Ice

    Arrive in Reykjavik from London, greeted by your Dream Tourism Representative. Enjoy a city tour, visiting landmarks like Hallgrimskirkja Church and Harpa Concert Hall. Experience the stunning virtual flight at FlyOver Iceland. Check in to your 3/4* hotel for the night and enjoy a delicious Indian dinner.

  2. Explore the Golden Circle and South Coast

    Explore the Golden Circle and South Coast. Visit Thingvellir National Park, Geysir geothermal area, and Gullfoss Waterfall. Continue to the South Coast to see Seljalandsfoss and Skogafoss Waterfalls, then end the day at Black Sand Beach in Vik. Overnight in Vik with an authentic Indian dinner.

  3. Jokulsarlon Glacier Lagoon, Diamond Beach & Skaftafell National Park

    Visit Jokulsarlon Glacier Lagoon to see floating icebergs and Diamond Beach with sparkling ice chunks. Explore Skaftafell National Park’s glaciers and waterfalls, or take a Plane Wreck Shuttle to the DC-3 plane wreck at Sólheimasandur Beach. Overnight in Hofn with breakfast and Indian dinner.

  4. Snaefellsnes Peninsula – Iceland in Miniature

    Explore the Snaefellsnes Peninsula, known as "Iceland in Miniature." Visit Kirkjufell Mountain and its waterfall, dramatic lava fields, fishing villages, and volcanic craters. See Hraunfossar and Barnafoss waterfalls. Return to Reykjavik for an overnight stay and Indian dinner.

  5. Blue Lagoon – Relaxation Like Never Before

    Relax at the luxurious Blue Lagoon, a geothermal spa amidst black lava fields. Enjoy the therapeutic waters and stunning volcanic views. Spend the evening exploring Reykjavik before your final night at the hotel

  6. Departure from Reykjavik

    Enjoy a leisurely breakfast before transferring to the airport for your return flight to London. Reflect on your incredible journey through the land of fire and ice, filled with unforgettable landscapes and cherished memories.

fields.itinerary:
1. Verdens Ende - Panoramic views at the western tip of Oslofjorden.

    Fly from London to Oslo, Norway. Embark on a round-trip boat cruise to Verdens Ende, Verdens Ende is a popular recreational area at the west coast of the outer part of Oslofjorden with panoramic views towards the sea in east and south. Enjoy a peaceful lake Verdens Ende trip nearby before returning to Oslo, a city rich in Viking history and modern architecture. After dinner, stay overnight in Oslo.

  2. Vigeland Sculpture Park - Over 200 sculptures illustrating human life and emotions. 

    After breakfast, explore Oslo, visiting iconic landmarks such as Vigeland Sculpture Park, home to over 200 unique sculptures that depict the human condition, and the Royal Palace, built in the early 19th century and the residence of Norway's monarchs. Visit Akershus Fortress, a medieval stronghold from the 13th century offering stunning views of the Oslofjord. At 3:30 PM, board a 17-hour cruise to Copenhagen, Denmark. Enjoy dinner onboard, scenic coastal views, and an overnight stay on the ship.

  3. Nyhavn - A vibrant 17th-century harbor with colorful buildings and historic ships.

    Arrive in Copenhagen, Denmark’s vibrant capital, and take a walking tour to explore its iconic attractions. Visit Nyhavn, a picturesque 17th-century harbor lined with colorful buildings and historic ships, and see The Little Mermaid Statue, inspired by Hans Christian Andersen’s famous fairy tale. Explore Tivoli Gardens, one of the world’s oldest amusement parks, blending nostalgia with modern entertainment. Later, fly to Aramsdram (assumed location) for an overnight stay, experiencing the local charm.

  4. Keukenhof Gardens - One of the largest and most beautiful tulip gardens in the world.

    Visit Keukenhof Gardens in the Netherlands, one of the world’s largest tulip gardens, originally part of a 15th-century hunting estate. Marvel at millions of blooming flowers in stunning displays. Take a scenic canal cruisae in Amsterdam, where the 17th-century canals, a UNESCO World Heritage site, offer picturesque views of historic bridges and elegant townhouses. Conclude your journey with a flight back to London.

fields.itinerary:
1. Arrival in Istanbul & Bosporus River Cruise

    After a warm welcome in Istanbul, check into your hotel and get ready for an enchanting evening. Embark on a Bosporus River Cruise, a magical journey between Europe and Asia, offering panoramic views of the city’s iconic skyline. Witness famous landmarks like the Dolmabahçe Palace and Galata Tower as the city lights twinkle. Enjoy a delightful dinner onboard paired with an energetic belly dance performance, showcasing Turkey’s vibrant culture.

  2. Exploring the Historic Heart of Istanbul

    Step into the city’s rich history with a visit to Hagia Sophia, a UNESCO World Heritage Site blending Byzantine and Ottoman influences. Admire its
    stunning mosaics and massive dome. Then, explore the magnificent Blue Mosque, renowned for its intricate blue Iznik tiles and breathtaking architecture. Wrap up the day at the Spice Bazaar, a lively marketplace filled with aromatic spices, Turkish delights, and colorful souvenirs.

  3. Cultural Gems & Shopping Extravaganza

    Start your day with a visit to the Istanbul Museum, where centuries of Turkish art and history come to life. Dive into shopping bliss at the Grand Bazaar, one of the oldest and largest covered markets in the world, featuring over 4,000 shops selling everything from jewelry to carpets. End the day with a tranquil walk in Gülhane Park, a lush green oasis with scenic views of the Bosporus.

  4. Leisure & Departure

    Spend a relaxed morning exploring Istanbul at your own pace. Take advantage of the free time to visit local shops, cafes, or simply soak in the city’s charm. In the afternoon, prepare for the next leg of your journey as you depart for London, followed by stops at Paris, Disneyland Paris, the Netherlands, and Belgium, where more adventures await.

fields.itinerary:
1. London to Milan to Venice (Overnight stay in Milan)

    Fly from London to Milan in the morning. After a warm welcome, enjoy a delicious breakfast before heading to Venice. Explore the city's iconic canals and landmarks for 2-3 hours. Afterward, enjoy a tasty dinner and check in to your hotel for a restful night in Milan.

  2. Milan to Switzerland – Scenic Bernina Express Journey

    After breakfast, take the Bernina Express from Milan to Switzerland, enjoying scenic views of the Alps. Explore St. Moritz for 3-4 hours, then travel to Zurich for dinner and an overnight stay at your hotel

  3. Interlaken, Grindelwald & Lauterbrunnen – Alpine Wonders

    After breakfast, travel to Interlaken, Grindelwald, and Lauterbrunnen, known for stunning lakes and 72 waterfalls. Enjoy breathtaking mountain views and explore the natural beauty. End the day with dinner in Zurich and an overnight hotel stay.

  4. Snaefellsnes Peninsula – Iceland in Miniature

    After breakfast, visit Rhine Falls and enjoy boat rides and views. Explore Lucerne's old town, Chapel Bridge, and Lion Monument. Return to Zurich for dinner and an overnight stay.

  5. Mount Titlis to London – A Stunning Farewell

    After breakfast, head to Mount Titlis for thrilling views and glacier exploration and experience panoramic views from the top, enjoy the crisp alpine air, and take
    in the awe-inspiring landscapes. .Return to Zurich and depart for London, ending your unforgettable Swiss adventure.

fields.itinerary:
1. Verdens Ende – Where the sea meets the sky in stunning, uninterrupted views. 

    Begin your unforgettable journey with a flight from London to Oslo, Norway. Then, embark on a scenic trip to Verdens Ende, where breathtaking panoramic views of the Oslofjorden await. Explore this peaceful area, known for its natural beauty, before returning to Oslo to unwind and enjoy a cozy overnight stay.

  2. Oslo – A dynamic mix of Viking heritage, royal history, and modern charm.

    Spend your morning discovering Oslo’s iconic landmarks, including the world-famous Vigeland Sculpture Park and the majestic Royal Palace. In the afternoon, travel to the picturesque village of Flam, tucked away in the heart of Norway’s fjord country, and settle in for a relaxing overnight stay.

  3. Flam Fjord – A breathtaking, serene cruise through Norway’s natural wonders.

    Wake up in Flam, a village surrounded by towering mountains and deep fjords. Explore the village’s quaint charm and embark on a stunning Flam fjord cruise, where you’ll be captivated by the serene beauty of the fjords and cascading waterfalls. Return to Flam for a peaceful evening.

  4. Norwegian Waterfalls – Witness the raw power and beauty of nature at its finest.

    Experience the magic of a Norwegian waterfall before making your way back to Oslo. After a final taste of Norway’s natural beauty, fly back to London with memories that will last a lifetime

fields.itinerary:

    Begin your adventure with an early morning flight from London to Milan. After arriving, meet your tour guide and board a comfortable bus to Lake Como. Spend 3-4 hours exploring the lake's crystal-clear waters, scenic mountains, and charming villages. Afterward, enjoy a delicious dinner before checking into your Milan hote for the night.

  2. Milan to Switzerland – Scenic Bernina Express Journey

    After breakfast, board the Bernina Express for a spectacular journey through the Swiss Alps, arriving in St. Moritz. Spend 3-4 hours exploring this glamorous resort town, surrounded by breathtaking mountain views. In the afternoon, travel to Zurich for dinner and an overnight stay.

  3. Interlaken, Grindelwald & Lauterbrunnen – Alpine Wonders

    After breakfast, travel to Interlaken, Grindelwald, and Lauterbrunnen, known for stunning lakes and 72 waterfalls. Enjoy breathtaking mountain views and explore the natural beauty. End the day with dinner in Zurich and an overnight hotel stay.

  4. Zurich, Rhine Falls & Lucerne – Nature and Culture

    After breakfast, visit Rhine Falls and enjoy boat rides and views. Explore Lucerne's old town, Chapel Bridge, and Lion Monument. Return to Zurich for dinner and an overnight stay.

  5. Mount Titlis to London – A Stunning Farewell
